[4] Ecuador
Date: Thu, 26 Jan 2006
From: Alfonso J. Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: El Diario, noticias, Ecuador. 26 Jan 2006 [trans. JGM; edited]
<http://www.eldiario.com.ec/?module=displaystory&story_id=59446&format=html>

The first cases of dengue fever have started to appear in Manabi.
Yesterday, the number of confirmed cases was more than 20.
Additionally, in the community of Portoviejo, an 8-year-old boy is
under observation because of a possible case of dengue hemorrhagic fever.
Dr. Melva Morales, an epidemiologist from the Health Authority,
confirmed that there are 4 cases in Portoviejo, 6 in Chone, 4 in
Santa Ana, and 5 in Manta, but reports from other areas are still
awaited, so the figures are not yet official.
The Leopoldo Izquieta National Institute for Hygiene and Tropical
Medicine also confirmed a case from Junin, in 11 de Febrero Street.
Cases in Portoviejo are from the following areas: 2 from El Naranjo,
1 from El Floron, and 1 from San Eduardo Street (LEA sector).
Dr. Morales also pointed out that preventive actions are being
carried out in all affected areas, not only in Portoviejo, which is
related to the fact that environmental fumigation is being carried
out only in Manabi, the capital city. "Environmental fumigation is
not the solution, it is helpful only in outbreaks; the important
thing to do is to tightly close water receptacles at home, to put
abate in tanks and water containers, to sleep under cover, and to
spray insecticides in households", she explained.
"Environmental fumigation is only for getting rid of the free-living
mosquitoes, but the next day thousands of mosquitoes are born in
breeding places," she added.
"3 vehicles from the Malaria Eradication and Vector Control Service
(SNEM, according to its Spanish initials) for environmental
fumigation have been working in Portoviejo since last Saturday. When
their work is done in this city, they will go to other places," said
Dr. Morales.
In 2005 there were 4000 cases of classic dengue fever, 75 cases of
dengue hemorrhagic fever, and 5 persons died. For environmental
fumigation, 400 dollars a week is needed to cover gas bills.
--
